data.enText: the state of being alone and not watched or disturbed by other people

data.chText: 她渴望过清静的私人生活。
data.enText: She was longing for some peace and privacy.

data.chText: 稍后，他在自己房间里私下读了那封信。
data.enText: He read the letter later in the privacy of his own room.
the state of being free from the attention of the public
freedom of speech and the right to privacy

simple_means.memory_skill: priv 单个 + acy 表性质 → 隐私

tr: the quality of being secluded from the presence or view of others
the condition of being concealed or hidden

value.def: If you have privacy, you are in a place or situation which allows you to do things without other people seeing you or disturbing you.

example.ex: He saw the publication of this book as an embarrassing invasion of his privacy...
example.tran: 他觉得这本书的出版侵犯了他的私生活，让他十分难堪。

example.ex: Thatched pavilions provide shady retreats for relaxing and reading in privacy.
example.tran: 茅草亭是独自放松和读书的阴凉清幽之所。

example.ex: ...a collection of over 60 designs to try on in the privacy of your own home.
example.tran: 能让你自己在家安心试穿的60多种款式的系列时装

value.def: If someone or something invades your privacy, they interfere in your life without your permission.

example.ex: The press invade people's privacy unjustifiably every day.
example.tran: 每天媒体都会毫无道理地干扰人们的生活。

value.tran: 干扰…的生活；侵犯…的隐私

trans: 私隱政策；隱私權保護；隐私政策；隐私条款；隱私政策

隐私权；隐私权理论；个人私事权；个人权利
